from tensorflow.keras.layers import Input, SimpleRNN, GRU, LSTM, Dense, Flatten, GlobalMaxPool1D
from tensorflow.keras.models import Model
from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import SGD, Adam

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
In [3]:
# Zbuduj zbiór danych
# To jest nieliniowy i długodystansowy zbiór danych
# (Właściwie przetestujemy wzorce długodystansowe i krótkodystansowe)

# Zacznij od małego T i zwiększ je później
T = 10
D = 1
X = []
Y = []

def get_label(x, i1, i2, i3):
  # x = sequence
  if x[i1] < 0 and x[i2] < 0 and x[i3] < 0:
    return 1
  if x[i1] < 0 and x[i2] > 0 and x[i3] > 0:
    return 1
  if x[i1] > 0 and x[i2] < 0 and x[i3] > 0:
    return 1
  if x[i1] > 0 and x[i2] > 0 and x[i3] < 0:
    return 1
  return 0

for t in range(5000):
  x = np.random.randn(T)
  X.append(x)
  y = get_label(x, -1, -2, -3) # short
#   y = get_label(x, 0, 1, 2)  # long distance
  Y.append(y)

X = np.array(X)
Y = np.array(Y)
N = len(X)
In [4]:
# Najpierw wypróbuj model liniowy – uwaga: teraz chodzi o klasyfikację!
i = Input(shape=(T,))
x = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(i)
model = Model(i, x)
model.compile(
  loss='binary_crossentropy',
  optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.01),
  metrics=['accuracy'],
)

# Trenuj model
r = model.fit(
  X, Y,
  epochs=100,
  validation_split=0.5,
)

In [7]:
# Teraz spróbuj prostego RNN
inputs = np.expand_dims(X, -1)

# RNN
i = Input(shape=(T, D))

# Metoda 1
# x = LSTM(5)(i)
x = SimpleRNN(5)(i)
# x = GRU(5)(i)

# Metoda 2
# x = LSTM(5, return_sequences=True)(i)
# x = GlobalMaxPool1D()(x)

x = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)
model = Model(i, x)
model.compile(
  loss='binary_crossentropy',
  # optimizer='rmsprop',
#   optimizer='adam',
  optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.01),
  # optimizer=SGD(learning_rate=0.1, momentum=0.9),
  metrics=['accuracy'],
)
In [8]:
# Trenuj RNN
r = model.fit(
  inputs, Y,
  epochs=200,
  validation_split=0.5,
)

In [10]:
# Teraz przejdź do problemu z dużymi odległościami

# Zacznij od małego T i zwiększ je później
T = 10
D = 1
X = []
Y = []

for t in range(5000):
  x = np.random.randn(T)
  X.append(x)
  y = get_label(x, 0, 1, 2) # long distance
  Y.append(y)

X = np.array(X)
Y = np.array(Y)
N = len(X)
In [11]:
# Teraz przetestuj ponownie nasz prosty RNN
inputs = np.expand_dims(X, -1)

# RNN
i = Input(shape=(T, D))

# Metoda 1
x = SimpleRNN(5)(i)

x = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)
model = Model(i, x)
model.compile(
  loss='binary_crossentropy',
  optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.01),
  metrics=['accuracy'],
)

# Trenuj RNN
r = model.fit(
  inputs, Y,
  epochs=200,
  validation_split=0.5,
)

In [14]:
# LSTM
inputs = np.expand_dims(X, -1)

# RNN
i = Input(shape=(T, D))

# method 1
x = LSTM(5)(i)

x = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)
model = Model(i, x)
model.compile(
  loss='binary_crossentropy',
  optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.01),
  metrics=['accuracy'],
)

# Trening
r = model.fit(
  inputs, Y,
  epochs=200,
  validation_split=0.5,
)

In [17]:
# Zwiększenie wartości T
T = 20
D = 1
X = []
Y = []

for t in range(5000):
  x = np.random.randn(T)
  X.append(x)
  y = get_label(x, 0, 1, 2) # long distance
  Y.append(y)

X = np.array(X)
Y = np.array(Y)
N = len(X)
In [18]:
# Now test our Simple RNN again
inputs = np.expand_dims(X, -1)

# make the RNN
i = Input(shape=(T, D))

# method 1
x = SimpleRNN(5)(i)

x = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)
model = Model(i, x)
model.compile(
  loss='binary_crossentropy',
  optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.01),
  metrics=['accuracy'],
)

# train the RNN
r = model.fit(
  inputs, Y,
  epochs=200,
  validation_split=0.5,
)

In [21]:
# LSTM
inputs = np.expand_dims(X, -1)

# RNN
i = Input(shape=(T, D))

# Metoda 1
x = LSTM(5)(i)

x = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)
model = Model(i, x)
model.compile(
  loss='binary_crossentropy',
  optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.01),
  metrics=['accuracy'],
)

# Trenuj
r = model.fit(
  inputs, Y,
  epochs=200,
  validation_split=0.5,
)

In [24]:
# GRU
inputs = np.expand_dims(X, -1)

# RNN
i = Input(shape=(T, D))

# Metoda 1
x = GRU(5)(i)

x = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)
model = Model(i, x)
model.compile(
  loss='binary_crossentropy',
  optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.01),
  metrics=['accuracy'],
)

# Trenuj
r = model.fit(
  inputs, Y,
  epochs=400,
  validation_split=0.5,
)

In [27]:
# Zwiekszenie T
T = 30
D = 1
X = []
Y = []

for t in range(5000):
  x = np.random.randn(T)
  X.append(x)
  y = get_label(x, 0, 1, 2) # long distance
  Y.append(y)

X = np.array(X)
Y = np.array(Y)
N = len(X)
In [28]:
# Test LSTM
inputs = np.expand_dims(X, -1)

# RNN
i = Input(shape=(T, D))

# Metoda 1
x = LSTM(15)(i)

x = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)
model = Model(i, x)
model.compile(
  loss='binary_crossentropy',
  optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.01),
  metrics=['accuracy'],
)

# Trenuj model
r = model.fit(
  inputs, Y,
  epochs=400,
  validation_split=0.5,
)

In [31]:
# LSTM z Global Max Pooling
inputs = np.expand_dims(X, -1)

# RNN
i = Input(shape=(T, D))

# Metoda 2
x = LSTM(5, return_sequences=True)(i)
x = GlobalMaxPool1D()(x)

x = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)
model = Model(i, x)
model.compile(
  loss='binary_crossentropy',
  optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.01),
  metrics=['accuracy'],
)

# Trenuj RNN
r = model.fit(
  inputs, Y,
  epochs=100,
  validation_split=0.5,
)
